<text>The provost is the chairman of the governing body of Eton College. He is chosen by the Crown and is assisted by a vice-provost and ten fellows.

==Provosts of Eton==

===15th century===

*Henry Sever (1440–1442)
*William Waynflete (1442–1447)
*John Clerk (1447)
*William Westbury (1447–1477)&quot;Thomas Barker&quot; (1447)

===16th century===

*Henry Bost (1477–1504)
*Roger Lupton (1504–1535)
*Roger Aldrich (1535–1547)
